HEADWORD: Tarriance
<hw>Tar"ri*ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or time of
tarrying; delay; lateness.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And after two days' <qex>tarriance</qex> there, returned.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarrier</ent>⟦br⟧
